parameters.description: logit annual survival probability of juvenile COTS
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Annual juvenile survival probability (unitless, on logit scale). Introduced to create a realistic maturation delay and better outbreak timing.

parameters.description: log initial juvenile COTS density at t=0
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Initial juvenile COTS density (indiv/m^2) for the new juvenile stage, estimated without using observations directly

parameters.description: log strength of density-dependent juvenile mortality (cannibalism/competition) per unit total COTS density
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Controls extra mortality among juveniles caused by conspecific crowding and cannibalism; applied to (C_t + J_t) in an exponential survival term exp(-k_can * (C + J)).

parameters.description: log exponential decay rate of rubble/stabilized substrate that blocks regrowth after coral mortality
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Controls how quickly rubble stabilizes/erodes and frees substrate for coral recruitment and growth; larger values mean faster clearance

parameters.description: logit fraction of coral mortality that becomes substrate-blocking rubble
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Fraction (0–1) of dead coral converted to rubble that temporarily occupies substrate; remainder becomes immediately available bare substrate

parameters.description: log initial rubble/stabilized substrate at t=0
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Initial rubble cover (same units as coral cover, typically % of substrate)

parameters.description: log amplitude of rubble-mediated juvenile survival boost
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Controls the strength of juvenile survival enhancement due to rubble shelter; after exponentiation A>=0 enters multiplicatively as (1 + A * f(R)). Set near -inf (very negative) to nullify.

parameters.description: log half-saturation rubble cover for juvenile survival boost
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation constant (same units as coral cover) controlling how much rubble is needed for strong juvenile shelter benefits

parameters.description: log Hill exponent for rubble-mediated juvenile survival boost
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Shape exponent (>0) controlling how abruptly juvenile survival increases with rubble availability; q=1 is gradual, higher q is more threshold-like
